text:
If you're looking for a school where your child will develop both valuable academic and life skills while building meaningful friendships, and looking forward to going to school every morning, look no further.

My son has been attending Little Gryphons Montessori since he was 3 years old. He's now 6 and preparing to say goodbye to the school and the friends he's made over the years. Looking back, I can say for a fact that I have never once regretted enrolling him at Little Gryphons (LG).

This is a school rooted in strong values, with lots of warmth and plenty of heart. It offers a safe, nurturing environment where children are encouraged to become confident, independent individuals. The transformation is evident — children who once arrived shy and unsure gradually blossom into bright, curious, and expressive little people who aren’t afraid to ask questions or share their thoughts. This is a testament to the school’s thoughtful unstifling approach and the positive influence of its teachers.

The school itself is well-maintained and spotless, with high-quality, mostly wooden materials that provide a calm and enriching environment for the children. I'm especially fond of the spacious layout, which emphasizes togetherness.

The teaching staff are nothing short of exceptional — nurturing, patient, and kind. They succeed in the challenging feat of making learning enjoyable for today’s children. A notable sign of the positive culture at LG is its low teacher turnover — in three years, I recall only one teacher being replaced. That level of consistency and stability speaks volumes, and is crucial in the children's development.

A heartfelt thank you to:
- Teacher Jameema, for your genuine interest in the children, your unwavering care, kindness, and dedication;
- Teacher Jess for sparking a genuine interest in Mandarin among the kids;
- Teacher Letchimi, for your irresistible bubbliness and bright energy (never change! :-));
- Peh Laoshi for your sweet, calm demeanour;

And of course, a big shoutout to Jacqueline and Terrence for setting up such a wonderful school. Little Gryphons was everything I hoped for when I was searching for a place where Adrian could thrive. I couldn’t be more proud of the thoughtful, curious, and happy little man he’s become.

To the whole Team LG: Keep up the excellent work. You’re shaping young lives in the most beautiful way - we will miss you all dearly!

- Adrian
